<br>
In particular, if your guild is making a natural progression outfitting other classes with epics --  hitting PoH/PoA for mage/enchanter/paladin/necro/ranger epics and PoF for shaman/enchanter/wizard epics and farming Kunark dragons to fill out the rare spells for caster spellbooks -- a lot of pieces will just fall in place.  If your guild is beyond the epic stage and doesnt bother with Kunark dragons your probably in a position to get an EB weapon anyway.<br>
<br>
We have went from 1 epic to 6 after a single PoA raid after collecting bits and pieces from hate/fear/chardok and killing sev when we got a chance.  <br>
<br>
You can lead a horse to water... we have 1 warrior that has a queen's blade -- hes a golem ball shy of an epic as we have a green scale, maestro hand, and wing blade for chaining but so many folks trash talk the epic he doesnt seem interested.<br>
<br>
I take it there is no resist check on enraging blow?   The only downside to the warrior epic is when fighting FR mobs.  Otherwise proc works well for me.<br>
