<br>
The PoI dragon can be done by any guild that has progressed passed the Kunark dragon stage. He is not that hard and he can be done every 4 hours. His loot is extremely nice for the effort (41% haste neck, EB hammer, 75hp/75mana ring, 75hp/75mana caster weapon). You could get a dozen spike drivers in the time it would take you to get 2 green scales.<br>
<br>
Grieg can be done with 3 groups if you know the fight. He is also very easy for anyone who is doing Velious bosses. Pops every 3 days if I remember correctly, and he also drops a bunch of really nice loot for the difficulty of the encounter. Ichorflow is about as common a drop as a green scale is so you could get as many Ichorflows as green scales in a given period of time.<br>
<br>
Vaniki is pretty cake now with AAs and levels. I haven't done him in ages, but we 3 grouped him pretty easily before SoL so 2-3 groups now should walk over him easily. Repop is ramdon I believe so you would have to camp him, but your chance of getting a Vaniki is as good as getting a shot at Sev since its unlikely he will be perma camped like Sev.<br>
<br>
Spend the time to get your epics for the sense of accomplishment and so you can have really cool looking light sabers. But don't go out of your way to get them to use, there are too many weapons that are far superior and easier to get. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=icsdave>icsdave</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/20/02 9:27:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4665.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is Epic Worth It??</span><hr size=1>   I think a few of you are a little to taken with lucy, it is NOT the source for spell data.   The info on the client side of eq is for display info no effect info.  What the spell does is SERVER side not client, the display is client. Spell data is WRONG on lucy on a lot of things because of this. To say that because lucy does not show an effect there for it is not there is in a word WRONG.  Lucy still list Rage of Tallon as a 2 min combat spell and IT IS NOT it is now worn not combat but Lucy does not show this!<br>
