<br>
From a personal accomplishment level, I think epic's are extremely worth the time and fun of doing them.  Nobody goes to PoA unless it's for epic fights and I would of never had the chance for freefall into the warm waters of FP were it not for epics.<br>
<br>
I think this has probably been argued over and over and over again and frankly it's a very easy answer in my opinion, if you're getting weapons for aggro, check the aggro weapon thread, if you already have 2 weapons, or can easily/quickly get, which have better taunt then the epic blade then from a strictly equipment based stand it's probably not worth it.<br>
<br>
Personally I still use both epic blades and swap them in and out with different combinations.  When farming I continuously use the dex buff from the blue blade to help my snare weapon proc.  When fighting without a dex buffer i'll swap the blue blade in for the dex boost with a taunt weapon in my primary.  With Pop and STA no longer being capped at 255, the 15 sta and 100 hp from epic isn't neccesarily something to pass up, espescially since willsapper, while being an awesome aggro weapon, only has 9ac and 35hp's.  <br>
<br>
Personally if I had it to do all over again I'd make a blond human warrior, get his epics and gnone skin armour and walk around calling myself luky skywalker...<br>
